egation among the\ncraters walls reach 8% brighter for Gallicum Labes and 2% fainter for Danuvius\nLabes. The Hapke parameter maps also show a dichotomy at the opposition effect\ncoefficients, single-scattering albedo and asymmetric factor, that may be\nattributed to the maturation degree of the regolith or to compositonal\nvariation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 3 Oct 2017 19:31:53 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-10-05"}
